# Nifillos — Project Instructions

This project uses **Nifillos**, a multi-agent orchestration framework.

## Quick Start

Type `/nifillos` to open the main menu, or use any of these commands:
- `/nifillos create` — Create a new cuadrilla
- `/nifillos run <name>` — Run a cuadrilla
- `/nifillos help` — See all commands

## Directory Structure

- `_nifillos/` — Nifillos core files (do not modify manually)
- `_nifillos/_memory/` — Persistent memory (company context, preferences)
- `skills/` — Installed skills (integrations, scripts, prompts)
- `cuadrillas/` — User-created cuadrillas
- `cuadrillas/{name}/_investigations/` — Sherlock content investigations (profile analyses)
- `cuadrillas/{name}/output/` — Generated content and files
- `_nifillos/_browser_profile/` — Persistent browser sessions (login cookies, localStorage)

## How It Works

1. The `/nifillos` skill is the entry point for all interactions
2. The **Architect** agent creates and modifies cuadrillas
3. During cuadrilla creation, the **Sherlock** investigator can analyze reference profiles (Instagram, YouTube, Twitter/X, LinkedIn) to extract real content patterns
4. The **Pipeline Runner** executes cuadrillas automatically
5. Agents communicate via persona switching (inline) or subagents (background)
6. Checkpoints pause execution for user input/approval

## Rules

- Always use `/nifillos` commands to interact with the system
- Do not manually edit files in `_nifillos/core/` unless you know what you're doing
- Cuadrilla YAML files can be edited manually if needed, but prefer using `/nifillos edit`
- Company context in `_nifillos/_memory/company.md` is loaded for every cuadrilla run

## Browser Sessions

Nifillos uses a persistent Playwright browser profile to keep you logged into social media platforms.
- Sessions are stored in `_nifillos/_browser_profile/` (gitignored, private to you)
- First time accessing a platform, you'll log in manually once
- Subsequent runs will reuse your saved session
- **Important:** Nifillos uses its own `@playwright/mcp` server configured in `.cursor/mcp.json`.
